annotation.TEXT: Yeah, it leads to the same place as the other door. (I'm sure they all lead here.)
I'm eating you too, to get revenge.
Whew, I managed to grab my reserve feather and the time barrels without horribly dying...
More purple buzzies... (I wonder if they're burnable or edible. Maybe I'll check another time.)
Screw the intended path, I have Yoshi!
Is this the end? And, let me guess, my remaining time is all I have to use on the boss, right?
And, we're back, with more Super SIG World 21! Now, let's see what the votes have to say about where I'm headed next...
There's another time barrel, and dang it, Mario! Stop catching the wall as I spin jump! Good thing even the upside-down piranha plants stay in their pipes if I'm near them in SMW!
Dang it! I want a feather, not a 1-up!
It's just like with Forest of Illusion 2's secret exit, except this one just leads to a Yoshi coin.
It's a desert, with Chain Chomps. Where have I seen that before? (2-5 in SMB3.)
Ow. And of course I get hit immediately after that flower has become unreachable...
So, I guess the gimmick here is a line-guided platform with a "Blackout Basement" effect on the line itself...
Close shave there. Is my foot still attached?
Nope. There doesn't appear to be anything interesting over here...
Now how am I supposed to get that Yoshi coin without the blue switch?
Also, that was a lousy attempt at the goal tape.

Alright, now both world 4 and world 5 were tied with two votes, so I'll be the tie-breaking vote, and I choose world 5, since I should've gone there after world 3 before, but I misremembered the voting results back then.
I could probably cheese the whole level by flying, but I'm going to try playing it out normally. (If I slip up somewhere, I can always Start+Select out!)
The last Yoshi coin, so I gotta be almost done...
I guess I'll finish up world 6 now. Let's enter the castle!
Okay, that unlocked a ghost house, but there's still the normal exit to find, and I'll try to see if I can find the "intended" method of reaching that secret exit (probably a P-switch).
It's a shame you can't even kill the Chain Chomps with a shell (you could in SMB3).
Yeah, but just 50 seconds, so I guess this gimmick continues.
And, since I, through some miracle, managed to hang onto Yoshi through the first level of a world, you can still vote on world 4 as well!
Ooh, that's a tricky jump. I think I'll switch to my cape for this one.

First the silly votes: (I'll put a 5 second pause annotation here.) 1 vote for me to reach level 85, and buy 99 mana potions and 1 tent, and sell 98 lives and 1 Yoshi, 1 vote for world 12034337 (1337 x 9001), 1 vote for me to find Yoshi a cake as worker's compensation, 1 vote for me to become a creeper and explode, 1 vote for me to realize a life-long dream of becoming a Yoshi Rider, 1 vote for not voting this time, 1 vote to take Yoshi to past levels and have him taste the wildlife, 1 vote for 3-1, and 2 votes for me to sing "You Should Drink Cucumber-Flavored Beer!" by IOSYS in the annotations.
So, we're done already? This level didn't seem very long, but that's fine with me.
What's that? A "Time" barrel, like the fuel barrels in DKC's Tanked Up Trouble? ...Oh! Time! Wow, I didn't even notice how little time I had left!
I have to be more careful in lower parts of the level due to visibility issues...
Well, for next time, you guys can vote on 5-2, or the ghost house (even if I cheesed that secret exit).
5-2 is now open, but I'm going to replay this level in search of all the Yoshi coins, and a P-switch.
The "fog" doesn't seem to extend upwards very far...

The "Cucumber-Flavored Beer" thing also got two votes, but I'm not gonna try to sing that in the annotations. I'm sure you guys can search for a video of it if you're interested. (It features Nitori from Touhou.)
Yep, it worked! Level breaking FTW!
No thanks. One flower is sufficient for now.
I was thinking about getting that feather, but decided to pass on it.
Whoa! How did I not get hit there? Who cares!
BARF! (How come ZSNES can't do the elongated key spitting out sound effect?)
Yes! Beat him! Well, that could've gone better, but at least I survived.
Okay, that jump is perfectly doable without a cape.
(Add classic Donkey Kong hammer song here.)
Good thing there doesn't appear to be any bottomless pits around here!
Alright, so here's 5-1, and it's a red level, so there's two exits to find. Better start searching!
Hmm... I wonder if scrolling the screen is a good idea...
Alright, well, let's get this Yoshi coin...
A partly cloudy water level in fact (somehow). Oh, I see that "secret" passage there!
Well, I'm stumped. If anyone knows where the fifth Yoshi coin and the P-switch are, let me know!
Also, I've hit another switch, so I can check out another one of these doors (and since I'm small, I can enter with Yoshi), but...
Gah! This is not a good time to get hit!
Once again, screw the obvious intended way, I have Yoshi!
Hey, I want a cape feather, not a poison mushroom!
To be continued...
Whoa, that's a lot of TT launchers. I imagine this part would be really tricky to avoid damage in without Yoshi.
5-GH
Something something something, something. Something...!?
"Hurry up!" Oh, I guess I've been in the level for long enough it seems.
And now the game's sending saws after me too! (And these aren't line-guided, so they can knock me off Yoshi.)
Sounds limiting, but that might mean I could afford to miss one or two of them, unless I need every single second I can get!
Yes, another feather, and a 50-second time barrel this time. (And I did need at least one of the previous two 10-second ones, or I would've timed out before reaching this one.)
Now, a mushroom is okay, but I want some real power ups, so just give me a moment...
I'm very suspicious of this pipe, but I don't see how you'd enter it...
Well, I found the secret exit! But, it looks like I'll need to locate a P-switch to actually reach it...
Nuts. I really want a feather.
There's a mushroom hidden there, but that's not exactly helpful...
For the serious votes, we have: 2 votes for 4-1, 2 votes for 5-1, and 7 votes for 6-6 (or finish up world 6). So, here's 6-6, which is a water level.
Yes, I will take the feather this time!
Nope. Didn't think so, but I wanted to check.
I wonder if that pipe is important...
Nuts. Yoshi can't eat them (that would've been so nice).
Still no sign of a P-switch or the fifth Yoshi coin. Anything beyond the goal? Hmm...
Two time barrels back-to-back? Ah, but these only give 10 seconds each.
Okay, I'm back here...
Okay, that was silly! I bet that guy isn't considered "dead" by the game, though.
...Or, I could totally break the level with this blue koopa that game was kind enough to give me! Sure, why not?
Well, that Yoshi coin was easy to find!
Gulp!
Oh, come on! Really? I can't believe that boomerang managed to barely reach me with its hitbox...
Yep, and we can see that another bridge segment has been added. Just two more bridge segments to go!
Yep, and ack! Four podoboos?! I was totally unprepared for that!
Well, I could sacrifice Yoshi (screw that!), or I could bring a blue shell over here and fly to it (I'll probably do that on a revisit).
And this reveals another warp star, and let me guess, it takes me to that level between worlds 1 and 2, right?
So, place your votes, and I'll start with the winning level next time!
There's the goal, but I only collected three Yoshi coins (though I saw a fourth), and I didn't find any P-switches.
Midpoint! Will I get a fresh time limit for the second half?
There's those silver munchers again, and of course I'm going to completely avoid them again. (I wonder if I should do a "science" with them at some point...)
Nope, but he's dead now!
Say... Yoshi can't eat these saws, can he?
Yeah, this is like Tanked Up Trouble, with the time limit acting like the fuel gauge, and grabbing that barrel gave me 50 more seconds. I'd better not miss any of them!
Careful! I really want to hang onto Yoshi here. He'll make getting through Torpedo Teds a lot safer.

Luigifan22222's translation: "I came through a doubtful factory zone and somewhat beat one of The Four Legendary Kings, Larry. Perhaps, are you called Larry because laritteru (mean: trippy) with a drug...!?
